The article announces the passing of Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg, a prominent figure in the US legal system. Ginsburg served as an Associate Justice of the Supreme Court for over 27 years and was only the second woman to be appointed to the Court. She was praised for her brilliant mind and powerful dissents, demonstrating the ability to disagree without being disagreeable. Her opinions, particularly regarding the legal equality of women and the disabled, have inspired many. Despite battling cancer and other challenges throughout her life, Ginsburg remained a fighter. The article expresses condolences to the Ginsburg family and hopes that her memory will be a blessing to the world.